    • canDispatch

      public static boolean canDispatch(MethodSignature called, MethodSignature potentialTarget, TypeHierarchy hierarchy)
      Warning! Assumes that for an abstract dispatch, potentialTarget is declared in the same or a subtype of the declaring class of called.

      For a concrete dispatch, assumes that potentialTarget is declared in the same or a supertype of the declaring class of called.

      Returns:
      Whether name and parameters are equal and the return type of potentialTarget is compatible with the return type of called.

    • resolveConcreteDispatch

      @Nonnull public static MethodSignature resolveConcreteDispatch(View<? extends SootClass<?>> view, MethodSignature m)
      Searches for the signature of the method that is the concrete implementation of m. This is done by checking each superclass and the class itself for whether it contains the concrete implementation.
